      "line": 168,
      "message": "typically, this is needed for code coverage.  However, PfKeyImpl (and its superclasses) define equals() to be abstract, so you are correct, lines 167-169 could be deleted, as they only test MyKey.equals, which is unnecessary.\n\nFor the next file, PfKeyUseTest.java, this is needed for coverage tests as equals() typically has an explicit check for \"this == other\"... except that PfKeyUse.equals() is implemented by lombok, so coverage doesn't matter.  Nevertheless, in that case, it's OK to leave the tests there, in case we ever change the definition of PfKeyUse.equals().",
